    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Modding suite for Hellcard, including editors enabling players to create new classes, artifacts, cards, enemies, and more.</p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Hexer Mod </h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >It also includes assets and sources for our Hexer mod. The mod itself is available in the Steam Workshop. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3039290/extras/70ea44c257eb574d511f92d0b534c775.avif?t=1753956810\" data-big-src=https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3039290/extras_big/70ea44c257eb574d511f92d0b534c775.avif?t=1753956810 width=800 height=450 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >While the Hexer mod is fully playable, it was created as an example to help and guide modders in their first steps. </p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Documentation and Assets</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Documentation, including guides, sources, and assets for the Hexer mod, can be found on GitHub. Links to documentation are available in the editor and the Steam community on the modding subforum. Sadly, Steam doesn't allow us to post them directly here. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p>",
